      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The weather will be sunny. The northerly wind has transported the new snow significantly. <br/> <br/> The fresh and older wind slabs are lying on soft layers. <br/> The solar radiation will give rise as the day progresses to rapid moistening of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> At intermediate altitudes there are 120 to 240 cm of snow, and even more in some localities. Snow depths vary greatly at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions, depending on the infuence of the wind."
      },
